# {DOMAIN} - Queue (Active Work)

> This is the branch read every single session. It holds what is active right now - nothing else. The Quick Resume at the top is the first thing a new session reads: it should let you pick up cold in under a minute. Completed items rotate down to Recently Completed, then out to the LOG once Recently Completed grows past ~5 items. Keep the whole file under ~80 lines.

## Quick Resume

The thirty-second orientation. Where things stand, what is the single most important next action, any one thing a fresh session must know before touching this domain.

- **State:** {one line - where this domain is right now}
- **Next:** {the single highest-priority next action}
- **Watch:** {any gotcha, blocker, or in-flight risk}

## This Session

Tasks planned for the current session. Write them here BEFORE doing them. Check them off as you complete them.

- [ ] {Task one}
- [ ] {Task two}

## Active

Work in progress that spans more than one session. Each item carries enough context to resume.

- {Active item - what it is, where it stands}

## Recently Completed

The last few finished items, newest first. When this passes ~5 items, rotate the oldest into `{DOMAIN}_LOG.md`.

- {Completed item} ({date})
